gurmukhi: hsq kIt ibKY bsY sB Taur sY inrDwr ]1]181]
transliteration: Hasat Koot Bikhai Basai Sabh Athaur Mai Nirdhaar||1||181||
translation: He abides in both the elephant and the ant, and be considered living at all the places. 1.181.

gurmukhi: jwiq pwiq n qwq jw ko mMqR mwq n imMqR ]
transliteration: Jat(i) Paat(i) Na Taat Jaa Ko Mantra Maat Na Mittra||
translation: He is without caste, lineage, father, mother, adviser and friend.

gurmukhi: srb Taur ibKY rimE ijh ckR ichn n icqR ]
transliteration: Sarab Thaur Bikhai Ramio Jih Charka Chihan Na Chitra||
translation: He is All-Pervading, and without mark, sign and picture.

gurmukhi: Awid dyv audwr mUriq AgwD nwQ AnMq ]
transliteration: Aadh Dev Udaar Moondat(i) Agaddh Naath Anant||
translation: He is the Primal Lord, beneficent Entity, Unfathomable and Infinite Lord.

gurmukhi: Awid AMq n jwnIAY AibKwd dyv durMq ]2]182]
transliteration: Aadh Ant Na Jaanooai Abikhaad Dev Durant||2||182||
translation: His Beginning and End are unknown and He is far away from conflicts.2.182.

gurmukhi: dyv Byv n jwnhI ijh mrm byd kqyb ]
transliteration: Dev Bhev Na Jaan-hoo-jih Maram Bed Kateb||
translation: His secrets are not known to gods and also the Vedas and Semitic texts.

gurmukhi: snk AO snkys nMdn pwvhI n hsyb ]
transliteration: Sanak Au Sankes Nandan Paav-hoo Na Haseb||
translation: Sanak, Sanandan etc; the Sons of Brahma could not know His secret in spite of their service.

gurmukhi: j`C ikMnr m`C mwns murg aurg Apwr ]
transliteration: Jachchh Kinnar Machchh Maanas Murag Urag Apaar||
translation: Also Yakshas, Kinnars, fishes, men and many beings and serpents of the nether-world.

gurmukhi: nyiq nyiq pukwr hI isv skR AO muKcwr ]3]183]
transliteration: Net(i) Net(i) Poukaar Hoo Siv Sakra Au Moukhchaar||3||183||
translation: The gods Shiva, Indra and Brahma repeat ‘Neti, Neti’ about Him.3.183.

gurmukhi: srb spq pqwr ky qr jwp hI ijh jwp ]
transliteration: Sarab Sapat Pataar Ke Tar Jaap Hoo Jih Jaap||
translation: All the beings of the seven nether-worlds down below repeats His Name.

gurmukhi: Awid dyv AgwiD qyj Anwd mUrid Aqwp ]
transliteration: Aadh Dev Agaddh(i) Tej Anaad Moondat(i) Ataap||
translation: He is the Primal Lord of Unfathomable Glory, the Beginningless and Anguishless Entity.

gurmukhi: jMqR mMqR n AwveI kr qMqR mMqR n kIn ]
transliteration: Jantra Mantra Na Aavaee Kar Tantra Mantra Na Koon||
translation: He cannot be overpowered by Yantras and Mantras, He never yielded before Tantras and Mantras.

gurmukhi: srb Taur rihE ibrwj iDrwj rwj pRbIn ]4]184]
transliteration: Sarab Thaur Rahio Biraaj Raaj Praboon||4||184||
translation: That superb Sovereign is All-Pervading and Scans all.4.184.

gurmukhi: j`C gMDRb dyv dwno n bHm C`qRIAn mwih ]
transliteration: Jachchh Gadadhrab Dev Daano Na Brahm Chhattrooan Maah(i)||
translation: He is neither in Yakshas, Gandharvas, gods and demons, nor in Brahmins and Kshatriyas.
